## Adding a New CLI Command

1. Create `cli/commands/mycommand.rs`:

```rust
use anyhow::Result;
use clap::Args;

#[derive(Args)]
pub struct MyCommandArgs {
    /// Your argument
    input: String,
}

pub async fn run(args: MyCommandArgs) -> Result<()> {
    println!("Input: {}", args.input);
    Ok(())
}
```

2. Update `cli/commands/mod.rs`:

```rust
pub mod mycommand;

#[derive(Subcommand)]
pub enum Commands {
    // ... existing commands
    MyCommand(mycommand::MyCommandArgs),
}

impl Commands {
    pub async fn execute(self) -> Result<()> {
        match self {
            // ... existing matches
            Commands::MyCommand(args) => mycommand::run(args).await,
        }
    }
}
```

3. Test it:

```bash
just run-cli mycommand "test input"
```
{% endif %}

