## Adding a New API Endpoint

1. Create `api/handlers/myhandler.rs`:

```rust
use actix_web::{get, HttpResponse, Responder};
use serde::Serialize;

#[derive(Serialize)]
pub struct MyResponse {
    message: String,
}

#[get("/api/v1/myendpoint")]
pub async fn my_handler() -> impl Responder {
    let response = MyResponse {
        message: "Hello from my endpoint!".to_string(),
    };
    HttpResponse::Ok().json(response)
}
```

2. Update `api/handlers/mod.rs`:

```rust
pub mod myhandler;
pub use myhandler::my_handler;
```

3. Update `api/routes.rs`:

```rust
pub fn configure(cfg: &mut web::ServiceConfig) {
    cfg
        .service(handlers::health::health_check)
        .service(handlers::my_handler); // Add here
}
```

4. Test it:

```bash
curl http://localhost:8080/api/v1/myendpoint
```
